**`Overall OAT Readiness`**

Based on the compiled execution logs and telemetry records detailed throughout the report, the definitive operational status of the platform is compiled as follows:

The Care Sphere Digital Health Portal successfully executed all mapped operational test items, achieving a 100% structural pass rate across all Infrastructure, Security, Performance, and Recovery tracks. No Critical or Major infrastructure defects remain open.

Subject to completion of all mandatory OAT activities and achievement of agreed acceptance thresholds, the Patient Portal subsystem may be recommended for production deployment.

Recommendation

Based on the documented outcomes of the OAT exercises, the successful resolution of all priority security vulnerabilities, and the verified performance stability under load, the OAT Engineering team certifies that the Patient Portal has achieved operational readiness. It is recommended that the subsystem be approved to proceed to live production deployment under the continuous monitoring of the DHA and Safaricom